<h1><%= @title = @cardset.name + ": Mechanics" %></h1><% mechanic_editor = permission_to? :admin, @cardset %><%= render :partial => "cardsets/setviews" %><% @cardset.mechanics.each do |@mechanic| %>  <div class="mechanic"><span class="mechanic_name"><%= @mechanic.name %></span><span class=mechanic_reminder"><%= format_text(@mechanic.reminder) %></span> </div>   <div class="mechanic_description"><%= @mechanic.description %></div>  <% if mechanic_editor %>    <%= link_to "Edit", edit_cardset_mechanic_path(@cardset, @mechanic) %>    <%= link_to "Delete NEEDS CONFIRM", delete_cardset_mechanic_path(@cardset, @mechanic) %>  <% end %><% end %><% if mechanic_editor %>  <%= link_to "Add mechanic", edit_cardset_mechanic_path(@cardset, @mechanic) %><% end %><br><hr><br><p>In card text or details pages, write the mechanic's code name between square brackets, like "[Crittercast]", "[Bushido 1]" or "Delay 4 {2}{R}{R}]". It will be expanded to the mechanic's name plus reminder text, such as "Suspend 4 &ndash; <%= format_mana_symbols("{2}{R}{R}") %>. <i>(Rather than cast this spell from your hand,...)</i>" <br>To expand a mechanic's name but not its reminder text, include parentheses at the end of the square brackets: "[Crittercast()]", "Delay 9 {R}()]".</p>